      "content": "That social resistance theory is interesting. It's possible people were just trying to avoid taxation or land surveys. To follow that thread, are there any specific historical accounts or studies of \"hidden\" populations in Virginia during that era? Like, people living on the fringes of the established townships who wouldn't show up in official documentation?",
